CommonFields.Title: Antistatic coating and electromagnetic shielding properties of a hybrid material based on polyaniline/organoclay nanocomposite and EPDM rubber
CommonFields.Author: Soto-Oviedo, Mauro A.
Araújo, Olacir A.
Faez, Roselena
Rezende, Mirabel C.
De Paoli, Marco-A.
CommonFields.Location: Laboratório de Polímeros Condutores e Reciclagem, Instituto de Química, Universidade Estadual de Campinas, C. Postal 6154, 13084-971 Campinas, SP, Brazil

Mixing.Description: twelve grams of organoclay were added to 350mL of water and vigorously stirred at 80C for 3 h, producing a fine aqueous dispersion
aniline and DBSA (molar ratio aniline:DBSA was 1:3), and ethanol (140 mL) were added into the clay–water dispersion at ambient temperature, and stirred for 3 h

Cooling.Description: following the stirring, the monomer-clay-water dispersion was cooled to ca. 0C with stirring

Additive.Description: an aqueous solution of (NH4)2S2O8 was added dropwise to initiate the polymerization

ChooseParameter.Other: the polymerization was carried out at ∼0C overnight, with stirring
at the end of polymerization, the dark green and very stable PAni-DBSA/organoclay dispersion was isolated by filtration
material was washed with an ethanol:water mixture (volume ratio 2:5)
product was finally milled in a mortar

Mixing.Description: PAni-DBSA/organoclay-EPDM nanocomposites were prepared in a counter-rotating twin-rotor internal mixer coupled to a torque rheometer (Haake, model Rheocord 90)

ChooseParameter.Other: the unloading of the mixing chamber was followed by lamination in an open roll mill at 70C

MoldingInfo.Description: flat 1.5mm thick sheets with 15 cm ×15 cm dimension were prepared by compression molding

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: used to measture dynamic mechanical properties at a frequency of 1 Hz with sinusoidal deformation and a heating rate of 2C per min, over a temperature range of −100 to 20C

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: diffractograms were scanned in 2-theta ranges from 1.2 tov10 degrees at a rate of 0.5 degrees per min

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: thermogravimetric analyses were done using a TA Instrument TGA 2050 at 10C per min, from room temperature to 900C under an air atmosphere

Electrometry.Description: used to measure the electrical conductivities of pressed pellets of PAni-DBSA/organoclay nanocomposites, according to ASTM F 43-99

SampleSize.description: Dynamic mechanical testing samples were rectangular bars (6.9 mm x 1.9 mm)
